==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water wing
<hw>Wa"ter wing`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>One of two
walls built on either side of the junction of a bridge with the bank of
a river, to protect the abutment of the bridge and the bank from the
action of the current.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water witch</ent>⟦br⟧
